observations.recommendation:
1. obtain the monthly statements
2. prepare the monthly Bank Reconciliation Statement regularly and submit the same to the Audit Team;
3. maintain the Subsidiary Ledger for each bank account that comprises the Cash in Bank – LCCA account;
4. prepare the Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) to record the transfer of LGSF to the General Fund and to restore the unreleased checks at the end of the year and reverse in the ensuing year; and
5. coordinate with the Municipal Treasurer to reconcile the difference of P802,807.52 and prepare the necessary adjusting journal entries.

6. enforce liquidation of cash advances from officials/employees who are still in service; 
7. issue demand letters to all officials/employees with overdue accounts, copy furnish the Audit Team and enforce pertinent sanctions as provided for under COA Circular No. 2012-004; 
8. ensure that employees with unliquidated cash advances shall not be granted another cash advance in accordance with the provisions of Section 89 of P.D. 1445 and COA Circular No. 97-002 to avoid accumulation of unliquidated cash advances; and 
9. exert all possible means to trace back records/documents relative to the unaccounted cash advances; if the liquidation of cash advances is no longer possible due to the death of officials/employees, request write-off as prescribed under Section 8 of COA Circular No. 2016-005.

10. provide depreciation on the PPE referred to in paragraphs 3.12, 3.13 and 3.14; 
11. prepare entries to recognize donated equipment from the Province of Leyte and DOH; 
12. record the AJE prepared for the transfer of PPE from Trust Fund books to the General Fund; 
13. derecognize the items costing below the capitalization threshold of P15,000.00 and recognize them as inventory; 
14. prepare adjusting entries to reclassify the incorrectly recorded PPE to their proper accounts; 
15. prepare entries to record the result of the reconciliation between the GSO’s records and that of the Accounting Office; 
16. submit the documents on the donated properties to the Municipal Accountant for proper recording in the books; 
17. ensure updated RPCPPE with complete information and unit value; and 
18. issue Property Acknowledgment Receipt for donated equipment and Inventory Custodian Slip for items below the capitalization threshold in lieu of the previously issued Property Acknowledgment Receipt.

19. transfer immediately the remaining unexpended balance of LDRRMF to the Trust Fund books; 
20. submit explanation to the Audit Team why the entire amount was not transferred to the Trust Fund books; 
21. immediately deposit the remaining funds to the depository account with the DBP; 
22. initiate the immediate transfer of the unexpended balance of LDRRMF to the Trust Fund; and 
23. include in the LDRRMFIP for every calendar year, under separate caption, the list of projects and activities charged to prior years unexpended LDRRMF.

30. submit justification why payment was made to these claims despite the deficient and lacking supporting documents; 
31. submit the lacking contract documents within five (5) days from receipt of this AOM; and 
32. moving forward, ensure that BAC submit original copies of contract documents and ensure all supporting documents to the contracts are completely filled out and compliant with the requirements of COA Circular No. 2009-001 and the RIRR of RA 9184.

34. ensure inclusion of Billboards, Occupational Safety and Health Standards as separate pay items in every infrastructure project; 
35. set up project billboard/signboard at project site for all projects of the Municipality in a standard format; and 
36. require compliance on Construction Safety and Health Program on all winning bidders to ensure that the workers of LGU projects are adequately protected against occupational risks.

43. maintain subsidiary ledgers for each component of the Road Network account and constantly update balances; 
44. compute depreciation of each component for the Road accounts from initial recognition and subsequent years and provide for accurate estimated useful life; and 
45. reclassify equipment and motor vehicles purchased in CY 2019 to the appropriate PPE accounts through adjusting journal entries (JEV).

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor should:
require the Municipal Treasurer to issue an official receipt on the remaining cash donations in the custody of the MHO and the immediate deposit to the depository bank;
require the Municipal Accountant to record the cash donations under the Trust Liabilities-DRRMF account, as well as its utilization; she shall see to it that utilization of the cash donations shall be thru a duly approved Disbursement Voucher with complete supporting documents.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

Maintain a Subsidiary Ledger for EACH bank account that comprise the Cash in Bank account;

Prepare monthly Bank Reconciliation Statements for all bank accounts, and close inactive accounts;

Prepare immediately the adjustment in the books of accounts for the erroneous entry made on the transfer of Loans worth ₱29,671,875.00 and other reconciling items in the BRS; and 

Coordinate with the Municipal Treasurer to reconcile and tally the balances between the Cashbook and the General Ledger and prepare the required adjustments oi the books.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

Trace back the transactions pertaining to all funds received from National Government Agencies based on source documents and the records maintained by the previous bookkeeper and reconcile with the General Ledger balance;

Prepare the correct adjusting entries on the unrecorded and erroneous recording of fund transfers and disbursements with net amount of ₱20,185,745.91;

Prepare Subsidiary Ledgers for EACH fund transferred from different National Government Agencies and monitor its disbursements and balances; and 

Supervise closely the work of the new personnel to avoid errors in recording all transactions of the LGU.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor through the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board and the SWM Focal Person, specifically undertake the following:

Follow-up the approval of 10-year SWMP so that the LGU could            immediately take the necessary actions to deficiencies noted if any;

Prioritize the provision of funds for the immediate establishment of a complete processing facility which includes the acquisition of a Plastic Shedder and Plastic Melter that will convert non-biodegradable materials into useful products in order to attain the objectives of the LGU’s  Ten-year Ecological Solid Waste Management Plan.
